caption.text:
August and September where full of events, but no matter how late it is from actual event, I will still post some impressions from #gamescom2019
Because there is nothing more precious than to stay true to the geek I am 😅
Unfortunately we did not manage to get into #cyberpunk2077 booth, the line you see is already 5-6 hour of waiting time... but what we managed to see and try out during these two days of #gaming:
1. Pagan Online - smth new for me from #wargaming
2. World of Tanks - our classic, it is already a tradition to visit the booth of this Belarusian gamedesigner :)
3. Humankind
4. Two point hospital - did u also play this gem on PS2 :B suuuuper fun
5. Darksiders Genesis
6. Watch Dogs Legion
7. Medieval - also a cute game from PS2
8. Hands-free gaming- see the video impression, your eyes control the game
9. Biomutant
10. Monkeyking
And some other fun mini and not so mini games.
We wanted to try out Doom, Borderlands 3, but wait in the line for 3 or more hours seemed too much of time waste, there is so much more to explore at Gamescom, so rather give a chance to small gamedevs, indie village or scatter around the merch area.

Book the trip love 💕 I have been so busy at work I really was slacking on my planning for my trips this month. I literally was still booking accommodations 2 days before I needed them. In my haste, I neglected to check my totalrewards site. So I booked last minute at 2 hotels that I will likely never stay at again. Even booked a smoking room by accident!! Smh. The next week I found that they do have a Harrahs in KC. I got this room for $15 amenity fee only per day and got a $5 per day food credit for not bothering housekeeping. I know better for next time!!! Even though it is attached to a #casino, hotel was pretty quiet & great buffet. It was about 15-20 mins from KC airport and where I needed to be. I know all the #gaming #travel hacks nationwide. caption.text:
A @avalanchestudios se consagrou com seus mundos abertos em Just Cause.Hoje em dia faz inclusive  consultoria e desenvolvimento coop em relação a esse aspecto, como é o caso de Rage 2. Mad Max também é de sua autoria e um excelente game.

Essa é a Edição de Colecionador de Just Cause 3 para Xbox One. Me divirto muito com o game pois, além de ser mundo aberto (uma das coisas que mais gosto nos games) é também cheio de ação.

Ela é composta por um mapa gigante em papel de Medici, um art book e um colecionável incrível da réplica do gancho de Rico Rodríguez. Esse ganho, aliás, é a assinatura de Rico nas suas aventuras (fazemos tudo com o gancho) além de ser a base da mecânica de gameplay da série.

Eu disse que ele tem paraquedas e wingsuit? 😆🚀

caption.text:
Sigil of the Faint Flame
Wondrous item, major, very rare (requires attunement)

Fitting within the palm of the hand, made of splendid gold, this sigil is encircled with 8 spirals set with perfect sapphires, and when held feels of sun-kissed warmth even in the coldest of shadows. 
This sigil regains 1d8+2 charges daily at dawn for the following property, and all charges are lost at sunset. While holding the sigil, you may use it as a spellcasting focus when casting spells dealing fire damage, gaining a +2 bonus to spell attack rolls and to their saving throw DCs.

Reprisal. When you take magical damage from a spell targeting only you, you can use your reaction to expend a number of charges equal to that spell's level to receive only half as much damage, and cast a fireball spell (save DC 15) of equal spell level back at your attacker, as part of the same reaction.

.
.
I tried and failed last year, but this year I’m really gonna give it my all! My goal is to post one picture a day for the month of October. I am following the official prompts, but the catch is I’m drawing all my video game characters that you have grown to love! 🥰
.
.
It’s really crazy to think that I used to do art as my main source of (unsustainable) income, but I really haven’t been creating anything new in the past few years. I’m going from 0 to 100, and I really need your love and support! 😭
.

caption.text:
Avez-vous passé un bon week-end ?
Moi ? J’en ai profité pour faire une petite escapade à #Cocolint 🏝
Car, même si j’y retourne assez régulièrement, j’ai été complètement conquise par ce remake : j’avais beau me savoir en terrain connu, j’ai apprécié le fait de redécouvrir l’île sous un tout nouvel aspect et d’explorer tous ses secrets, une fois de plus 💕
En observant l’Oeuf du Poisson-Rêve depuis la Plage Coco, j’ai eu une pensée émue pour tous ceux qui ont foulés ces terres pour la première fois ces derniers jours. J’espère que vous avez vécu la plus belle de toutes vos aventures et qu’elle vous marquera profondément, comme cela fut mon cas il y a vingt-cinq ans de ça.
Au loin, le cri d’une mouette résonne dans le ciel azur, comme pour faire écho à une ancienne promesse. Le sourire aux lèvres, je sais que je ne l’ai jamais oublié... 🐚
.
.
.

Such a wonderful and beautiful game. It calls “The Island of El Dorado” or “The Thieves of El Dorado” and it’s one of the most beautiful games I’ve ever played. The box was completely black with golden letters. It has an magnetic lock and in the inside every peace had his own place. Here you can see how I played the character “Stella the adventures”. Also every piece was so lovely made and had a nice haptic. The course of the game reminds me of “Settler of Catan” but with many new twist. 
In the Cafe @zamgwuerfelt in Munich you can test and play this wonderful game. So be free to try this out. ——————————————-

caption.text: So ends the September 2019 season. Regardless of the limitations imposed by Operation Blue Skies, we still had many players reaching legends and getting personal bests. We ended with over 45k clan points and 5467 globally. A few people tried to improve their personal best as season reset. They sign up for legends and gem their army to do their 8 attacks quickly. This part of the process is dependent on luck, attacking before taking defence. Mostly the attacks are against th12s, but lucky for a th9 to find another th9.
